   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LIFE-STUDY OF JEREMIAH MESSAGE SEVEN ISRAEL'S SIN AGAINST JEHOVAH</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>AND</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>JEHOVAH'S PUNISHMENT UPON ISRAEL 2 ISRAEL'S RETURN</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>OR JEHOVAH'S CORRECTION FOR HER APOSTASY Scripture Reading: Jer 3:6 4:31</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>In 3:6 4:31 we see that Israel could either return to Jehovah or receive His correction for her apostasy.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>God's correction is a matter of His chastisement.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>I. ISRAEL THE WIFE'S APOSTASY</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Jeremiah 3:6-11 speaks of Israel the wife's apostasy.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>To commit apostasy is to leave the right way and go another way; it is to leave God and turn to idols.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>In this section of His holy Word, Jehovah as a Husband deals with the apostasy unfaithfulness of His treacherous wife.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>A. Israel Having Been Divided</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>into Two Kingdoms</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Israel had been divided into two kingdoms: the north was called the kingdom of Israel, and the south, the kingdom of Judah.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>B. The Northern Kingdom of Israel</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>Becoming the Apostate</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The northern kingdom of Israel became the apostate and committed spiritual fornication adultery with idols vv.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>6, 9 .</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>The idols were Israel's evil lovers.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>Israel should have had only one husband, but instead she had many lovers, many idols.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>C. The Northern Kingdom of Israel</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>Being Divorced by Jehovah</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Because of her fornication, which polluted the land, the northern kingdom of Israel was divorced by Jehovah vv.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>8a, 9 .</S>
   </TEXT>
